# Delivery And Quality Checks

For this project, completed code/content changes should be treated as production-bound unless the user explicitly says not to deploy, push, or commit.

## Default Delivery Flow

- After making requested edits, run the most relevant available checks before finishing. Prefer `npm run build` / Astro build for site changes, plus diagnostics for edited files.
- If checks pass and the user has not said otherwise, commit the relevant changes and push the branch so Vercel/GitHub can deploy them.
- Keep commits focused. Do not mix unrelated dirty-tree work into the same commit.
- If the working tree contains unrelated changes, identify them and leave them untouched unless the user asks to clean them up.

## Final Quality Gate

Before the final response, explicitly verify:

- The implementation matches the user's latest request, not an older interpretation.
- The changed page or feature is discoverable at the URL/path the user expects.
- The branch is clean or any remaining uncommitted changes are explained.
- The latest commit has been pushed, unless the user explicitly asked not to push.

## If Something Cannot Be Verified

- Say exactly what could not be checked and why.
- Do not imply a deploy happened until the commit is pushed and the remote branch includes it.
- If a command fails because tooling is unavailable, try the repo's known local Node path before giving up.
